{"title":"Exclusive Ibis Hakka MX Gravel Bike with Silver GRX LTD Group Available for $3,899","link":"https://bikerumor.com/exclusive-ibis-hakka-mx-gravel-bike-silver-grx-ltd-group-jensonusa/","date":1692365430000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1000\" height=\"562\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build3.webp\" alt=\"Ibis Hakka MX Shimano GRX LTD\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build3.webp 1000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build3-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build3-800x450.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build3-120x67.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build3-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build3-400x225.webp 400w\" /></p>\n<p>If you’re looking for a unique gravel bike that’s available off-the-shelf, the latest exclusive from Jenson could be it. No, this is not some sponsored post, just an interesting build we spotted for a tempting price. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build2.webp\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build2-800x450.webp\" alt=\"Shimano GRX LTD\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build2-800x450.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build2-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build2-120x67.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build2-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build2-400x225.webp 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build2.webp 1000w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build1.webp\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build1-800x450.webp\" alt=\"Shimano GRX LTD\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build1-800x450.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build1-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build1-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build1-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build1-400x225.webp 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build1.webp 1000w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In May of 2022, Shimano introduced a<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-grx-limited-polished-silver-gravel-groupset/\" target=\"_blank\"> limited edition of their GRX gravel group</a>. Instead of the blacked-out appearance of the standard group, GRX LTD included extensive polishing to make it predominantly silver. We haven’t seen much of it since the launch, which makes sense if it’s truly a limited edition. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build5.webp\"><img width=\"1000\" height=\"1000\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build5.webp\" alt=\"Ibis Hakka MX Shimano GRX LTD\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build5.webp 1000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build5-297x297.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build5-800x800.webp 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build5-120x120.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/Ibis-Hakka-MX-Shimano-GRX-LTD-Jenson-build5-768x768.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, you can get your hands on a complete <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/first-look-new-ibis-hakka-mx-monstercross-bike-unveiled/\" target=\"_blank\">Ibis Hakka MX</a> with the GRX LTD group for $3,899. According to Jenson, the retail price of the build is $5,435, so it seems like you’re getting a solid deal. You’re also getting a bike color combination that is less likely to be spotted out in the wild. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Currently, the website lists 53, 55, and 58cm frame sizes as in stock, and all of them come in the Coal colorway for the frame. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://jenson.sjv.io/c/2227671/989438/13009?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jensonusa.com%2FIBIS-HAKKA-GRX-LTD-JENSON-EXCLUSIVE-BIKE\" target=\"_blank\">jensonusa.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/exclusive-ibis-hakka-mx-gravel-bike-silver-grx-ltd-group-jensonusa/\">Exclusive Ibis Hakka MX Gravel Bike with Silver GRX LTD Group Available for $3,899</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"979ed6f903982fa1efed234a71da9f4148cf2ce49405a21e480c7018828ed5e6","category":"Cycling"}